Sentencas: A general procedure for the extrusion of Ce0.8Gd0.2O1.9 tubular electrolytes is detailed.
Titulo: Fabrication and properties of Ce0.8Gd0.2O1.9 electrolyte-based tubular solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Using a commercial water-based binder system, Ce0.8Gd0.2O1.9 was extruded, then fired at 1600 degrees C to form high-density electrolyte tubes (98% relative to theoretical).
Titulo: Fabrication and properties of Ce0.8Gd0.2O1.9 electrolyte-based tubular solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Heat-treatment of the Ce0.8Gd0.2O1.9 powder at 900 degrees C for 4 h yielded tubes that were highly dense with a smooth surface finish, while non heat-treated powders resulted in an extrusion that was less dense with poor surface finish.
Titulo: Fabrication and properties of Ce0.8Gd0.2O1.9 electrolyte-based tubular solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Electrodes were applied and the tubular SOFC was electrically tested.
Titulo: Fabrication and properties of Ce0.8Gd0.2O1.9 electrolyte-based tubular solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: A good open circuit voltage of 0.911 V was achieved for the cell, however a poor operating current density of 0.0123 A/cm(2) at 0.7 V was obtained.
Titulo: Fabrication and properties of Ce0.8Gd0.2O1.9 electrolyte-based tubular solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The results demonstrate the potential of fabricating and operating tubular SOFCs.
Titulo: Fabrication and properties of Ce0.8Gd0.2O1.9 electrolyte-based tubular solid oxide fuel cells
